<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> review.their <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span> are a bit strange but have been confirmed by one of the bartenders. this information is not available on the website: mon, tues, wed: 5-8pmthurs: 1-8pmfri: 5-7pmsat/sun: 1-5pmduring the above <span class="highlighted">hours</span>, all pints are $2 off and all goblets are $1 off.this is probably the best dive bar for brews that i've found. there is nothing fancy about this place. it's dark and has a bit of a retro feel upon entering. there are bar stools along the bar and a few tables scattered throughout. bartenders are nice, helpful, and knowledgeable.there are many draft beers on tap and a nice variety of ales. i'm told that they rotate several taps about every 3 wks. it feels like a neighborhood joint where everyone knows each other. they don't serve food per se, but they do sell pretzels for $3 and serve free peanuts. they have one pool table and, remarkably, they offer free pool every day, all day.parking - free street parking
