i found this place on yelp since it's the game haus cafe. &nbsp;parking can be tough since it's all metered or street parking (free neighborhood street parking if you are willing to walk a couple blocks). &nbsp;we arrived at 6:30pm on a saturday evening and they had <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> until 7pm! &nbsp;woohoo! &nbsp;yay for places that have <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span> seven days a week! &nbsp;the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu had $5 appetizer items, beer, wine, and well drinks. &nbsp;we ordered the chicken wings and olympia beer combo (only $5!), the frickles (really yummy! &nbsp;i suggest getting the regular size order for $3 more rather than the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu small order) the mini burger, and tots. &nbsp;i also ordered the $10 fried chicken sandwich, which was pretty large and came with homemade chips. &nbsp;i got to try the grapefruit beer and the strawberry beer (grapefruit was better - the strawberry was too sweet and tasted more like a cider). &nbsp;service could've been better - we had to go to the bar to order every single time, and the bartenders weren't all that friendly. &nbsp;overall, i liked the ambiance and beer selection, and best of all, the frickles! &nbsp;i would come back here just for those!
