i came to granville for dinner on a tuesday night with a friend. the restaurant wasn't very busy, and there were many open seats. we made it just in time for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>, which basically is a few bucks off an alcoholic beverage. we check in on yelp and got the free side of sweet potato fries, which were delicious! very well-seasoned, would definitely recommend getting them. i decided to try the uptown mac since it was well reviewed on yelp. to be honest, i wasn't too impressed. i got a bit full from the fries so i could only eat about half of the plate. the mac &amp; cheese was a little bland in my opinion, the pieces of chicken helped the dish out (brought some salt to the taste buds). compared to other mac &amp; cheese places i have had, this plate was mediocre. my friend went with the pork chop. it was very very tender (chewy almost), and very good. the cooked spinach and mashed potatoes on the plate were good as well. this was a quite a filling plate, decently priced for its portion.overall service was nice and consistent. remember to validate parking if you are parking in the american structure!
