two things drew me into this new find: it was listed as &quot;hot and new&quot; on yelp and the sign outside read: &quot;daily soup: whiskey.&quot; sure, why not? and there i went, descended down the stairs to the moose den....the moose den marketed itself as a whiskey bar, but turned out to be a let down. <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> deals were weak. a buck off wines, house drinks, draft and well drinks 4-7pm and all day monday. meh. house drinks are weak. the menu featured basic drinks, and didn't even have their own special old fashioned or manhattan. how are they a whiskey place??the best whiskey drink on the menu they had was a rusty nail, which was simply cutty dark scotch and drambuie on the rocks. with the store front name the moose den and them making it a whiskey bar, a whiskey aficionado would not impressed by their selection and drink choices. however, mac and cheese from scratch was good, and the bartenders were friendly.there's definitely room for improvement. i'd like to see some craft cocktails added to the menu. the set up is already there. dart boards and shuffleboards are there and with a big screen tv for weekend sports game.
