no clue why this place doesn't have a higher rating, the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is amazing! 12-7 every day is 2-for-1 drinks, 2 beers for $5 and 2 well drinks for $3. shots are included too! the food is pretty good for a bar, the nachos are probably my favorite. they also have really good french fries and hot wings. haven't really tried anything else but at a bar, i think that's all you need. overall the service is pretty good, sometimes it can be hard to get the bartenders' attention when it's crowded but they do walk around making sure everything is okay. only downside is my favorite bartender left, the others are great but hope was definitely one of the best. first time my friend and i came here we had way too many drinks but she made sure we were okay and gave us glasses of water without us having to ask. if hope was still there it would definitely be a five star place, but the other bartenders are still great and the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is amazing. they also have drink specials after <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> ($5 jack and coke on fridays!) so it makes it one of the best bars around town!
