this review is for the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. that being said, i am not one to be sold on presentation alone. if the food looks great on the plate, that's nice and everything, but i'm more concerned with the taste and price. i thought barbix was expensive for what it was. they don't have a very good selection of <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu items (although the glass of moscato i ordered was probably the most delicious moscato i've ever had). the food is prepared to look super upscale and trendy, which is exciting when it first comes out, but once you start eating, it's not at all impressive. we ordered a few things off the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu (which only applies if you sit at the bar), and ended up quickly paying and going somewhere else. why the quality of a restaurant's <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is so important is because it allows me to try their food without paying $30 for an entree. if i like the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> food, i will come back (hopefully with a date, a girl can dream) and spend money for a full dinner. i honestly was not impressed with barbix at all. some place so cute should have better service and tastier food. and the people raving about their deviled eggs have clearly never been to a southern bbq! who puts a sardine on a deviled egg?? who?!
came here a couple mondays ago for $1 oysters and <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>.between my friend and i we ate 24 fanny bay, 6 beausoleil and 6 eld inlet oysters. our favorite ones were of course fanny bay oysters from vancouver. they are creamy and full of juice! although <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> suppose to run all night, but the night we were there. the $1 oysters special ran out an <span class="highlighted">hour</span> after it started. making it ultra special for us to be able to gobble down 3 dozens oysters and drank 805 in to a <span class="highlighted">happy</span> monday night. we also tried the delicious bone marrow and crispy fries. all that was amazing... and i wouldn't mind going back again to try their other delicious <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> specials.
i went here on a weeknight for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> and i loved it. the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is great--glasses of wine are anywhere from $4-$6! i went with a large group and the staff was super accommodating, letting us sit outside and still order <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. the outside area is super cute and great on a summer night. we ordered a variety of dishes, including: burrata, brussels sprouts, saffron arancini, a charcuterie plate, and 2 cheese plates. everything tasted delicious, especially the crispy brussels sprouts and burrata. definitely try this place if you are in the area--great drink deals for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. the food isn't cheap but it's very good. to save some money, i recommend street parking instead of valet.
came here for monday night <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> and was very pleasantly surprised. the place is warm and inviting, dark wood inside, and a nice patio with fire space heaters. we were greeted by the host as soon as we came up to the door, and seated at the bar when we told them we were there for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. he let us know we had 15 minutes left to order and the bar tender was super attentive and patient, letting us sample 2-3 wines before we finally made up our minds. the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is great, with 1/2 off glasses of a wide array of wines. another nice surprise was that monday was 1$ oyster night. &nbsp;this was just an added bonus. i have to say, they weren't the best oysters i've had during <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> ---- they were a little beaten up due to poor shucking and there was less brine/liquor than i would've liked in the shells, but combined with the rest of the experience...still a solid 4 stars. &nbsp;this place is already on my list of brunch places to try and i can't wait to come back!
