3.5 stars rounding up.i had dinner here with 3 girl friends last night. found meter parking closeby on the street and only had to pay $1.50 (it's free after 8pm) which is better than the $6 valet parking!we had reservations so we got seated right away but there were still a good amount of tables available. we thought we were going to order drinks from the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu but it turns out <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is only if you sit at the bar! bumble-bummers. but i ordered a glass of prosecco anyway. mmm gotta love the bubbly!their menu has a bunch of small plates so we got a bunch to share.crostini misti - 3 crunchy little bread pieces with different toppings on each. they were okay for the most part. wouldn't order it again.hamachi crudo- it was a little too fishy for our taste. but the avocado was a nice touch!shrimp &amp; chickpea flour tortillas w/ cilantro tzatziki - the tzatziki sauce was delicious and essential to the dish! i think it would have been kinda plain without it. if you're korean, this dish looks and tastes a lot like bu-chin-gae!sweet potato and rapini hash - rapini is like little broccoli. this was like a little side dish of mostly cubes of sweet potato. this was a-okayyy.grilled broccolini w/ chili, garlic, lemon aioli. this one was my fave of the night! and everyone else loved it too! who would have thought broccolini would be so good? but it was because of the aioli! sooo good! i think i could dip anything in that sauce and it'd be deeeelicious!pappardelle pasta w/ dungeness crab w/ artichoke hearts &amp; fresno chilis and mint. this was the most filling dish of the night (and the most expensive). the pasta is a little on the plainer side but it tasted pretty good. i think overall, the restaurant is best for an intimate date. ambience is dimlit and romantic, kind of on the plainer wooden side but it's still nice and cozy. service was extremely quick and also very friendly and pleasant. all the food came out super fast and we never had to wait around for anything which was nice. we were done in less than an <span class="highlighted">hour</span>! overall, i'd give this place a try again - maybe next time i'll sit at the bar for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> and try more from their wine selection. :)
