this bowling alley is a hybrid of a typical old-school bowling house &amp; a more state-of-the-art round 1 entertainment establishment. it's like an old-school bowling alley because of the house equipment(balls, shoes) which is old and grimy like other bowling alleys. there are plenty of lanes(34) that are maintained accordingly for the several leagues set up throughout the week. the oil used on the lanes are real bad however. it seems heavily oiled so when your ball returns, you get all this grease on your hands. really disgusting actually.the nice part about this place is that it's brand new. the bowling area is small but is very clean, and modern. it also seems like the owners are trying to preserve it as much as possible before it breaks down into the familiar dirty, rundown bowling alley like most bowling alleys become.i really don't like the user interface. it's really confusing and hard to follow but i guess it can be really cool and entertaining to kids.prices are fair but lookout for specials such as $1/game wednesdays all day.the highlight of this bowling alley is the bar. it is a large area which could be it's own building. there is also a wide variety of beers on tap(over 50 or 60) with some good specials and <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span> throughout the week.
