&quot;roscoe's rocks my socks!&quot;not to be mistaken w/ chicken &amp; waffles. this place is all about the sammiches! ginormous...delicious...sammiches! practically everything on the menu - entr&eacute;es, appetizers, salads and drinks, are served super-sized! and if you're a big sports fanatic, well then this is the place to be at during game-day. i don't know why it took me song long to try this place. my husband and i came in on a friday evening (and again on sunday!) hoping to score good seats for the laker game. we had just come from buffalo wild wings and that was a total fail. hella crowded and the wait-time was ridic!!! surprisingly it wasn't too crowded at roscoe's and we found seats at the bar right away. what's great about this place is no matter where you sit or what angle you're facing, you've got a good view of the game. started off with a round o' beers and a free bag o' peanuts. they had about 25-30 beers on tap. we likey! i tell ya, there's no better way to drink a cold beer than in a big, frosty mug. and i'm talkin' huge manly mugs! a 64oz stella for the hubby and a 40oz black velvet for me. so crisp and refreshing! the 40oz is served in a chalice, which made me feel very royale! now, onto the food! i ordered the martini - grilled chicken breast, mozzarella cheese, lettuce, tomato, drizzled with a balsamic glaze and pesto mayo, sandwiched between two thick slices of grilled parmesan bread (like sizzlers!). can you say ... omgawd-licious! it was soooo friggin' good that i had to take my eyes off the game for a bit and savor the awesomeness that was going on in my mouth. wow. one of the best sammiches i've ever had and for $11.95, hell it was worth every penny! my husband ordered the wfc burger ($11.95)...loved it! when we came back for sunday's game, he ordered the classic patty melt ($10.95) and said that it was just as good as the wfc! i agree! i just couldn't resist, i ordered my martini again...mmm. all burgers and sammies comes with a slice of pickle and one side. one huge side that is. for the tinier appetites, you have the option of splitting w/ a buddy. there's a $2 split-charge, but... you still get a full-sized portion of your side and you and your buddy can choose different sides! the curly fries are fantastic (w/ lots of ranch) and the onion rings and macaroni salad were seriously, the best i've ever tasted. i hear their house chips are pretty bomb too. everything we tried was super! the prices aren't cheap but imo, very reasonable, especially for the quality and quantity! special shout-outs to our two awesome waiters/bartenders, cody and michael. thank you for your top-notch service, your friendly smiles, and for making them killer drinks! can't believe you guys don't have a <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>...bummer. roscoe's deli has all the elements of what me and my hubby look for in a sports bar - great food, full bar w/ a good selection of beers on tap, awesome service, big-screen tvs (w/ audio during games!), and a very laker-friendly staff and atmosphere. sill luv heroes in claremont but roscoe's is now our new fav sports bar...and it's much closer to home! yay!***live entertainment on weekends out on the patio***breakfast served on sundays 'til 1pm***atm on site
