i've heard good things about this place many times. tonight, i drove by and noticed a big ol' parking spot right in front just waiting for me. it was a sign for me to stop and have a drink.valet is not free! it is $3!there are seats outside and more in the back, along with another bar. anyway, i strolled on in and was greeted by the bartender and a friendly waitress. the place is dimly lit and gives off that &quot;sexy&quot; vibe. it's a perfect place for a date or for a casual night with friends. i ordered a 'salted pisco peach lemonade' which was absolutely delicious and stiff, just the way i like it!after that, i asked the bartender, sam, if he could make something for me that was not on the cocktail menu. he asked me if i liked ginger beer and i told him i had never tried it before. he let me have a little sip of their house ginger beer and i loved it (i love ginger, though). sam told me this drink was part of their old menu and called it the &quot;mescal mule.&quot; bottom line: the drinks were stiff and delicious. the service was great and i was able to find parking outside.i will give it another try next time for their <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>.
