lunch time!the ambiance:i had come to hyperion public before but late night for some drinks. i had a moscow mule and it was good. yesterday i came to check out their lunch menu. we tried the avocado fries($12; panko-crusted/ lime-cilantro aoli) &nbsp;as an appetizer and for entree i had the turkey burger ($14; house-made turkey patty/havarti/grilled onions/avocado/arugula/tomato) and he had the btla sandwich ($13; applewood bacon/avocado/romaine/tomato/sriracha aoili/toasted sourdough).the avocado fries were lightly breaded and i liked that. the turkey burger was just okay until i tasted the caramelization of the bun with the havarti cheese. that changed the flavor and it went from just okay to good. the ingredients tasted fresh. the btla was also good and he liked that it had a lot of bacon. the entrees came with a choice of fries or mixed greens. since we had the avocado fries we chose mixed greens. the mixed greens was exactly like the costco spring mix (maybe it is from costco) and they use a light dressing. when he was eating his salad he bit on a piece of wood and it hurt his tooth. we believe it was a piece of the stick they use to hold the sandwiches and burgers together. our server apologized and offered us a free dessert. he chose the salted caramel ice cream, which comes with chocolate pieces. i believe our server was the manager and he did a great job making sure we were taken care of.the tips:<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is monday-friday from 4-7pm. they have a set menu and it is $5 and under. also, bottomless mimosas every day until 3pm! &nbsp;lastly, they have karaoke on thursdays at 10pm. hmmm... might have to check that out. parking sucks in this area so just uber-it.
