the reviews about this place are really all over the place. &nbsp;being there myself about 4-5 times since they first opened last year, it really makes me think that the people who don't love this european concept may just not be ready for it. &nbsp;the place is located in the heart of the village and it has a very casual atmosphere in a totally european, chill way. &nbsp;everything i've tried so far has been delicious and my all time favorite is the chicken salad. yum. &nbsp;they have incredible cheese and meat boards as well as pastries to die for. &nbsp;on to the service part - yes, you have to order everything at the counter and they bring it out to you. &nbsp;that's how it is in a lot of european inspired places and i don't see how this is such a negative for so many people on here. &nbsp;you get fantastic service at the counter, you sit and enjoy tranquility without having a server hovering over. &nbsp;it's exactly what i personally enjoy. &nbsp;for people who need more attention, you can always sit at the bar. &nbsp;the bartenders are all very friendly, at least that has been my experience. &nbsp;go see michelle, she'll muddle up an amazing cocktail and even play some quirky and fun game with you!! the last time i went, they had started a great <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> with complimentary appetizers from 4-7pm monday - friday. what?? amazing, that's all!!
