i love this place!!! &nbsp;this has been one of my go-to &quot;special&quot; occasion restaurants for the last 15+ years. &nbsp;the lawry's family, owner of the fancy bev. hills prime rib place owns this restaurant as well. &nbsp;i believe it was their very first one. &nbsp;the prime rib menu here is identical to the one in bev. hills. &nbsp;the cool thing about their dinner menu is that it constantly changes with the seasons. &nbsp;i highly recommend a souffl&eacute; for dessert.if you want a quick lunch and drink, i highly recommend the sandwich bar for lunch or <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>.prices are a bit pricey but this place is a first class restaurant. &nbsp;service is first class. &nbsp;portions could be a bit bigger but fair compared to other restaurants in this price range. &nbsp;valet parking $3 (i think).
a classy establishment. if you have an affection for the uk and pub/tavern like places and the constant sunny southern cali weather is driving you crazy then i recommend you head on over to this restaurant and bar right away. dark inside. lots of little rooms. i met a lady here who had been coming back to the tam every year for 35 years around the holidays. she says it's a magical, festive place around christmas, and if you're going to come here you should definitely go then. a special occasion. i could see hanging out at this bar. especially if you like beer. the brisket sandwich was delicious, savory and full of flavor, the meat tender. friendly staff too. everyone was smiling and pleasant. note: this place has <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> monday-friday 4-7pm. there's a parking lot, but it's valet and i'd recommend finding street parking. this area isn't too bad. you can do it. and it's way cheaper. do it. go here. now. (10:35 am? too early? oh, yeah. they open at 11am i believe - is this correct? you have time.)
i like tam's. &nbsp;it's a pretty good place. &nbsp;go during <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> (4 - 7) and beers are only $5/pint. &nbsp;they serve guinness and belhaven scottish ale. &nbsp;if you get there before 5, you can get the lunch menu. &nbsp;if you order a sandwich such as roast beef, brisket or corned beef, they have a chef come to the carving station and cut the meat right there in front of you. &nbsp;i've been here a few times. &nbsp;when it's crowded, it's loud. &nbsp;last time i was here was before 5, and the place was near empty, and quiet. &nbsp;the few folks that were there were decidedly older and more mellow. &nbsp;i struck up a conversation with a few of them, and found that one of them was from my old neighborhood where i'm from - only he was 20 years or so older than i. &nbsp;the meat sandwiches are good. the fish &amp; chips is also fantastic. &nbsp;they also serve the same hand made potato chips that they have at lawry's. &nbsp;i would definitely recommend this place, have been back a number of times, and will continue to go back.
