as a current little tokyo/arts district resident, i've always felt that a good dive bar was the only thing missing in the 'hood. so when i heard this bar was opening up shop right across the street from me, i jumped for joy!i made it out here yesterday for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> after work with the bf because he needed to watch the niner game somewhere closeby. while they do have tvs, i must note that they are on mute. they also don't have hh menus but you can just ask the bartender for that info.there were only a handful of other people there so it did feel kinda dead but it was a monday evening on a holiday week.bathrooms are clean and smell nice, there are hooks for your bag at the bar, and there is an outdoor smoking area which faces 2nd street for you smokers. i thought that was actually the entrance but it's over more to your right if you're facing the bar outside.
i really love the decor of this place. when i walked in i could smell the newness of all the wood working in there. i could tell a lot of though went into the design and the over all feel of the place.so we ended up here on xmas eve at <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. i had the cuba libra which was fantastic. it had perfect balance of sweet, acid, and effervescence. i lot of times if i ask for a cuba libre at other places, they basically had you a rum and coke. then for my second drink i had their house special highball, which is johnnie red and soda, which was also good, as to be expected.i think wolf &amp; crane is a wonderful addition to little tokyo, and i look forward to visiting them in the future.
