i work in california plaza, the building next door to this wonderful restaurant, and have been here 3 or 4 times already. this is my go-to place for lunch dates with friends and the closest place i can hit with my coworkers for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. i would give it 5 stars for service, 5 stars for great tasting food at decent prices, 5 stars for the abundant choice of indoor and outdoor seating, and 5 stars for the chill, yet yuppie crowd that dines here.everything i've had here has been super good. the burger is my favorite! it has a really juicy patty (i always get it medium) and perfectly toasted bun. the french dip sandwich and country fried chicken rolls are also really good. i really like the deliciously soft and subtly sweet hawaiian rolls on the fried chicken rolls. also, the fried chicken inside is really fresh and surprisingly light (as in not overly greasy like kfc). all dishes come with a refreshing salad. i love the dressing they put on it.<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> drink prices are slightly more expensive than other <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> places in downtown (it's $5 for beer and well cocktails, $6 for house wine, $7 for specialty cocktails here), but i'd be <span class="highlighted">happy</span> to come here and pay an extra dollar on a drink for the convenience, service, and atmosphere.
