ok honestly, this place is like, super mega awesome. for the record, i was already pretty drunk when i went (<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>), but i don't think that really matters. the restaurant itself is really chic and young -- kind of like an expensive loft and a submarine had a baby that was raised in soho but now lives in la (but not west la). very industrial chic. you'll get that reference when you visit. the food was amazing; very flavorful/fresh/portioned well/presented cute/salty (in a good way)/emotional/drunk food/awesome. i had the chef's burger (eaten without the top bun with a fork and knife, duh), pastrami gravy fries (i know), baked crab dip (to balance out the land meat), and two mango jalapeno margaritas (martinis? unclear about that). it was everything. our waiter was super helpful and by &quot;helpful&quot; i mean &quot;cute&quot; but no for real though, he was actually super helpful (cute). all in all, chic vibes, good burgers, fierce drinks, helpful (cute) staff. biiiyeee xo
updating my review. a day after i wrote my review, i was contacted by the assistant manager, winston. he wrote a very nice message to me and invited me to come back. basically, i was just extremely impressed by his professionalism and his friendliness. he invited me to return at any time &amp; he would have a seat saved for me. he wanted to help me (a dtla local) find something i loved the menu. so...did i?well yes, i did. i returned with my friend &amp; we got to try different drinks + food. the moment we walked in, we were greeted very well. winston guided us to the table he had reserved for us (he even asked me where i wanted to sit in our email chain). i had a bad experience last time with the drinks so winston let me try 3 different drinks. i ended up really liking the nat's hard cider. it was hoppy, not too sweet, and just a really good drink. i highly recommend it. from the snacks/apps portion: 1) beer nuts ($3.00: sweet, salty wasabi) - these were alright. you can pass on them.2) cucumber, kombu, dill pickles ($3.00) - these were quite good! i recommend trying them if you like pickles. they definitely taste different than you're average pickle...but i personally enjoyed trying them.from the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu:1) da buck fity wing ($2.50/each - ask your server for more details. these are only available on certain days so call in advance if you want to try one of these) - man these are huge. when you go to a wings place, you probably have to eat 3 wings to get the same fill from plancheck's wing. plancheck is known for their &quot;da buck fifty wing&quot; &amp; i can see why. it is quite delicious. i recommend trying this!from the burger menu:1) bleuprint burger ($13.00: smoked blue cheese, pig candy, fried onions, roasted garlic steak sauce, peppercress) - i feel like i should've tried a different burger. my friend tried it and liked it a lot. i took it home to my sister, and she devoured it. so i recommend getting this is you like having a light blue cheese taste. it definitely isn't too cheesy. last time, i tried the k-bbq burger and the plan check burger and i would say the bleuprint burger is the best out of these three.2) truffle/wine burger - (not a regular menu item) it was a little bit too cheesy.3) fries - average fries. nothing special. ketchup tastes a little strange.i was too full to try a dessert.i am glad i came back because i definitely would say that i will come back now. i have found things on the menu that i enjoy. i am just not a huge fan of burgers in general...so don't take my word for it (the burger portion)pros: great service, good food, lots of options, different than a typical burger joint like counter or umamicons: no free parkingconclusion: definitely stop by here, grab a drink and enjoy a nice meal with some friends! :)
we came here for the hello kitty hunt event, but unfortunately we decided that the cost and meal option offered for the hello kitty pin was not worth it. especially with the fact that we couldn't choose what burger we wanted when all their other burgers sounded so much more amazing. setting:street parking may be hard to find, but there is a public parking lot on the left of the restaurant but it is $8 for parking.upscale and modern restaurant. lots of windows and natural lighting. lots of tables and benches. i just dislike how tiny the tables are, but at least the food isn't served on giant plates that barely fit. they do have a really nice bar as well.service:our server jj was very nice and conversated with us about the event going on and gave us pointers on the food. it was very awesome of him to offer us the hello kitty green tea lattes because we chose not to get the exclusive meal deal. we also had multiple servers refilling out waters and asking if everything was good.everyone seemed clean cut and professional.food:(<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> 3pm - 6pm)da buck fity wing $1.50 each- buffalo flavored whole wings (you get the whole arm!)these were served hot. i don't usually like buffalo sauce because most of the time they have too much vinegar which makes them tangy, but it was light and perfect here. it was a great appetizer.beast fries $6.66- schmaltz onions, bacon spread, and americanized cheesethese tasted like beer cheese fries. i didn't like the cheese too much but i did like the flavors from the bacon spread. this dish was quite small. it was ok.truffle mushroom swiss burger $14portabello mushrooms with truffle oil and veggiesthis definitely has to be one of the best burgers i have ever had in my whole life. its quite a simple burger but was melting in my mouth with every bite. the truffle flavorings was so subtle, tasting almost like a garlicky goodness. the burger buns here are also very unique. they are light and covered in a type of grain. all i can really say is, you must try this burger!!korean bbq burger $14add fried egg $2- grilled pork belly, kimcheese, sprouting onion, gochujang bbq sauce, peppercressthis was another great burger! the bbq sauce was sweet. the grilled pork belly was juicy and savory. the patty is cooked to perfection. not too dry and not too undercooked. it was just juicy. everything just went so well together.hello kitty green tea lattethese came in cute plastic cups. green tea on the bottom, whipped cream on top with green tea hello kitty shaped powder. the tea wasn't exactly sweet. it just tasted like a milky green tea. the powder is a bit bitter if you taste it by itself. but its decent when you mix everything together.overall, i would definitely come back here again!it just kind of sucks that none of their burgers or sandwiches come with a side of fries. all sides are sold as an a la carte. the burgers are on the smaller side as well, but you definitely get your moneys worth in quality and flavor.
