visited this place for dine-la event last week. i was super excited about it, because i love new orleans food, and their menu seems to be very promising. food:here's what we ordered from the dinela menu1st course: avocado toast and garlic chips and dip. the avocado was bland, and the toast wasn't very crunchy. garlic chips and dip was your average bag chive and onion chips with a side of dips. not impressed with either.2nd course: pork belly bites and charred cauliflower. the pork belly bites were placed in lettuce, it's quite enjoyable, though a tad bit salty. loved the charred cauliflower. 3rd course: duck and grits, crab meat. the duck and grits is my favorite out of everything here. duck was a bit dry though. &nbsp;crab meat smells a bit fishy, and a tad too salty. venue:love, love, love the venue, decoration, atmosphere. it's located on a land in between the two streets, with beautiful large windows. the decor truly reminds me of being in no. drinks:i think this place is the perfect place for a quick <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> drink, catch up with your friends. their cocktail is too sweet, but you can request it otherwise.service:very attentive service, our server came and check up on us a few times.
came here at the suggestion of a local who loves this place. &nbsp; the venue is awesome, and the service is great. &nbsp;the food is ok. &nbsp;i'm a southerner, so although the owners are from no, the food is meh. &nbsp; i did the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> tour, which included the smoked shrimp beignets, corn fritters, fried oyster po'boy, and the crab cake. all of the food is heavily breaded, much more so than i'm used to when eating food from new orleans. &nbsp;flavors are good, but after two of the fritters i pushed them back. &nbsp;i tore open the beignets to pull the shrimp out and i took the oysters off of the roll and ate them separately. &nbsp; the crab cake was nice. &nbsp;more of a bar food feel than a great no experience. &nbsp;the service and energy make it worth the visit.
i booked a sunday birthday brunch here and was hesitant because i don't often have brunch dtla. &nbsp;the atmosphere was to die for and the service was really fantastic. &nbsp;the manager took really great care of my party of seven and our waitress was lovely and attentive. &nbsp;probably the best aspect of the brunch was the new orleans style jazz trio that was playing in the upstairs dining area while we were there. &nbsp;that, together with the airy french quarter feel, made it a great birthday location. &nbsp;the cocktails are fantastic and the selection of mimosa flavors were great for sunday brunch. &nbsp;though i am generally not a fan of ginger, you must try the ginger mimosa...a friend said it was the best champagne drink she has ever had. &nbsp;the only thing that was a little weak was the food. &nbsp;quality was good, but timing was a little off and the flavor's were nothing to write home about.bottom line...go for the drinks and atmosphere!! &nbsp;i will definitely go back for a <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> drink and app or brunch again.
a breath of fresh air in an otherwise smoggy downtown la. preux &amp; proper gives angelinos a reason to go downtown. the food is creative and tasty, the staff is friendly and at times hilarious and the drinks are the most refreshing. i love the amount of abita beer that is on tap, such a selection. the specialty cocktails is where it's at though. the west side is a drink that you drink everyday in the summer and never regret the hangover the next morning. as for the food, i tried the shrimp beignets because everyone said to. amazing. i then had the fried chicken sandwich. holy crap. you guys, when that is on the menu, you need to order that. i also went to the event called rhythm &amp; booze last tuesday. i mean come on, such a fun event. a late <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> and music from brother sal just set the mood for the night. the crowd was live and loving every minute of it. i can't wait to go back for the next one. seriously go check this place out and bring a group of people to maximize the effect!
