n a water or the drink i ordered... and keep in mind i told the waitress as i was ordering how upset i was that others were helped first and how long we had been waiting. next a staff member came out with fries... and again tried to deliver it to the 3 top with the women.. who politely said it was not theirs... and the runner took the fries outside... and at this point i felt those must be ours as well... i attempted to stop the runner; but he just went back to the kitchen with the fries..i looked at my watch it was now 6:28pm... i had no drink... no water... no food... no service... i asked a different staff member to have the check for the beer because we wanted to leave.we waited about 5 minutes and the waitress came over and said &quot; i am so sorry, we have a new system and i was not aware. you will not need to pay for the beer.&quot;i said, &quot;i am very disappointed. my husband loves your po' boy ... and that is what he wanted. this is the 3rd time this has happened to us at your restaurant. we live right across the street and i have to tell you we are not going to be coming here anymore because of this terrible service&quot;.the waitresses said, &quot; i am sorry. the other times you have been here were you sitting down here at the bar or upstairs?&quot;i said, &quot;the bar&quot;.she said, &quot; that is why. they have not really figure out this part yet&quot;.my husband interrupted her and said &quot;well we try to support local businesses. and by not 'figuring it out' you need to tell the owner this will run him out of business, like the last restaurant that was here the parish!&quot;she said&quot; i am very sorry. would you like to speak with the manager and tell him this yourself?&quot;i said sure. but i was saying it in a really annoyed way. she said &quot;i will get him so you can tell him, and maybe he can 'do something' for you&quot;.we waited for about 5 minutes and left.i was not 'looking for something'!!!!!! i wanted 1 beer 1 blackberry whiskey smash 1 po' boy and 1 fry.... during &quot; <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>&quot; and now it was 6:40 and all i had was a half a beer.... i wanted out!this is just another l.a. restaurant; it is not staffed correctly... the quality control is not there... and you can not treat people like this.  i wish the manager would have spoken to me and made it right.note for management: if you have read this far you can see on my check in logs the exact times and days (with the exception of 3/6/15) that i was in your restaurant. i figure we spend on average (for just the two of us) $80 per visit and i always tip starting at 20%. last year we went to &quot;peking tavern&quot; 25 times. (check my check ins)you just lost about $2000 in sales from us. $400 plus of tips for your workers. lastly you lost my recommendation as well as somewhere i will bring people.
