villains is a pretty decent bar.service is super duper slow! you have to order at the bar and there is usually only 1 person working. free street parking.<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is until 8 pm daily. has food and drink deals. all food items are $5 for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>.fries - decent fries. seasoning was lacking but my wife swears they are usually really good.sliders - they ran out of slider buns so they gave us the villains burger. the sliders have the same toppings. the grilled tomatoes are good. they make the burger. everything else is basic.brusslesprouts - seasoned very well. the glaze is sweet, which cuts the bitterness off the sprouts. beer is $1 off. prices range from $6-8 normally. they were out of a lot of beers which is pretty dumb for a bar. you can add a shot for $4 bucks but you do not get the dollar off from hh.highlight is the $1 heineken light chips. girls walk around and give you chips for $1 cans of heineken light which you get at the bar.would be an awesome bar if they fix the slowness.
