absolutely love this place, cannot recommend it enough.yes if you're looking to get crafty and make your own six-pack, this is the perfect beer store to do it. but i absolutely love the bar aspect of it. you get to peruse and pick a bottle/can of beer from hundreds and hundreds of different kinds of beer from breweries. there's a $2 corkage fee for every beer (beers can run anywhere $1.50 and up). so it ends up being a really good deal, great way to try new beers, and a fun place to hangout with people. they have a little patio and have a bunch of board games to play. ideal place to day drink and depending on the people, a fun date-idea.they have '<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>' monday-friday 4-7pm where there's no corkage fee. a great place to stop before or after a dodgers game.also it's byo-food...so you can bring you own stuff, or even order delivery and enjoy you food inside.
may be the best west la beer hole-in-the-wall since tda. all bottles are sold individually - perfect for when you want to try 12oz of a pricey brew without committing to the whole pack. the tap bar is limited, but well curated.great selection, decent prices and corkage free <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span> mean you can open a bottle and have a seat in their cozy bar after searching through the shelves.if you are the kind of soul that searches in agony at cap n cork, trying to decide what bottle to choose, then you may know peace here. you can sit down and just try them all.
so glad this place exists. sunset beer company is always my first stop when i go beer hunting. i usually just make quick stops in the bottle shop during the day, and haven't had a chance to hang out in the lounge area yet, but it looks like a great place to hang with other beer folk. i've been on a mission to try a different beer everyday, so i'm thankful that they have such a wide selection of loose cans &amp; bottles. i've tried some wacky stuff here that i would likely never have committed to a 4/6 pack of elsewhere. staff is very helpful and friendly. it's actually surprising how many people work here, considering the size of the space. this would be a great place to bring a friend to split a bomber. $2 corkage fee is very reasonable. waved during <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span> too. my only complaint is that it is tough to find parking. they have a very small with only 2 dedicated spots. both always seem to be full, it has 1 entrance/exit, so it's a pain to get in and out of during busy <span class="highlighted">hours</span>, and street parking is not always available in the area. other than that, this place is a local treasure.
