me and my mister managed a date downtown for a grand sum of $20, including tip! how's that for frugal? many thanks, pour haus, for rewarding our <span class="highlighted">hours</span> of perambulations with a <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> wine and scrabble bout!pour haus has that typical poured concrete urban look to it, with high ceilings and the typical urban hipsters dudes pouring the vino. there's a nice little patio for your imbibing pleasure if you've brought along your pooch or it's one of those sultry los angeles nights. adjacent to this is a garden where they clearly grow some of the produce used in their gastronomical creations.twas quite nice to be greeted with a sample our (just a wee taste) of their sparkling offering for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>, a lambrusco. i ended up getting the regular red, which was just a basic glass of red, nothing remarkable, but hey, it was a $5 glass of wine in a cool, clean environment, so i have no complaints. we were also greeted by a nice bowl of truffle cheese popcorn, which the mister devoured with much gusto. he was even offered a second bowl of aforementioned popcorn.a plethora of board games provides many options for mental engagement. my poor mister, thinking he could defeat me in scrabble just because he bingoed out early in the game. what can i say? he's a novice at few things, but scrabble is definitely one of them.<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> is daily from 4 - 7, and you can select from a red, white, sparkling or a beer for just $5, plus there were an assortment of <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> priced bites you could also try. there are some vegan things on the menu as well, but we did not partake...
