a decent wine bar.my friends and i stumbled upon this place after a recommendation from a friend. my friends and i usually like to order a bottle wine. this establishment is different in that they do not have a wine list. they have their bottled wines showcased against the wall and you just walk over and look at the wine and pick one that you like. the prices are on the bottom of the bottle. they have a fairly decent wine selection. the staff was extremely friendly and nice. they also gave us our space without giving us the stink eye even though we ended up staying there for awhile. some of the things that makes this place unique are their complimentary truffle popcorn (which is actually pretty good), a free tasting of one of their dessert wines when you are first seated, and the fact that they have boardgames. kind of weird seeing board games at a wine bar but it was quite entertaining. my friends and i ended up playing cards of humanity... not a good combination while drinking wine... haha :)the downfall was their food. we tried a whole bunch of their appetizers off their <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu (<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> daily from 4-7pm). we tried their greek nachos, oxtail tacos, mac&amp;cheese, slaw salad, flatbread, sloppy joe, and smores. the food wasn't bad but it wasn't particularly good. all of the dishes were average at best. with improvement on their food this place has potential to be awesome!
