whilst searching for a fun <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> spot to visit with mis amigos, i came upon the love song bar in a yelp search. thanks, yelp! i am <span class="highlighted">happy</span> to report that the love song is hipster heaven just south of skid row, gentrified enough to feel completely safe, but still gritty enough that it's not a scene (yet). the setting is vintage and unique (i so hope they keep that upright piano in use every once in awhile), <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> prices are decent, and bartender is friendly. he seemed a bit off his game the night we visited, but it wasn't disastrous or anything. just sort of a having to order twice and then getting the wrong drink kinda thing. it didn't bother me: bourbon is bourbon. the seating is ample and comfy, lots of pillows. definitely a great spot to hit if you like to drink in a low-key and cozy setting!
it is sure nice to see broadway undergo a measure of revitalization. &nbsp;the creep has been slow, but really apparent as of late. &nbsp;the love song bar is a notable outlier on the street, and a fine bar. &nbsp;it expectedly has the hipster vibe with young bearded fellows about, and an old school <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu with drinks based on your grandparents' favorites, and at pleasantly reasonable prices. &nbsp;the d&eacute;cor is a juxtaposition of cool, turn of the century wood bar on the right, complete with deer antlers, and an almost mid-century feel of green lounge on the left. &nbsp;oh, and the bar has a nice collection of vinyl in lieu of a jukebox, where you can select an lp and play it on one of their turntables. &nbsp;bring your own if you like... &nbsp;the folks there have none of the pretense apparent in some other bars staffed by the lumbersexual types, and are simply welcoming and friendly. &nbsp;hit them after four for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>, and enjoy five dollar cocktails. &nbsp;oh, and don't miss the chance to check out the wallpaper in the men's room.
