nice place. &nbsp;immediately greeted at the door. all i wanted was some takeout. ordered within 3 minutes of walking in.awesome! &nbsp;then i saw the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu &quot;4-6pm - oysters $1.00&quot;. yes please. &nbsp;i'll have some while i wait for my food!oysters came very quickly. &nbsp;they're shucked right in front of you. &nbsp;they come beautifully served with sides of hot sauce, freshly grated horseradish (yum) and red wine vinegar with shallots. oysters were firm and meaty. &nbsp;i'll be back for this <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> special, for sure.for my dinner i ordered the side beet salad with arugula and goat cheese ($8,) a side of black beans ($4) and a side of plantains ($5)beet salad was perfect. &nbsp;great beet to cheese ratio. &nbsp;balsamic vinaigrette did not overpower.black beans - i didn't think such a small serving of black beans should be $4. &nbsp;i still don't, but the rich flavor of the beans made me forget about the price. plantains were a letdown. &nbsp;they didn't really have a lot of flavor. &nbsp;they either weren't ripe enough or they were not cooked long enough to really let those sugars take hold. &nbsp;i did not devour these like i am known to do.i mean, i still ate them, but it was more of a &quot;meh, i should eat this since i paid for it&quot; instead of a nom nom nom kinda thing. &nbsp;i'll definitely be back here. &nbsp;nice atmosphere, good food, attentive staff and great <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> specials.
i absolutely love this place! everytime we've been here the service is always spot on and it's always <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> which is the plus side all the time! the <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> menu offers a good amount of options to explore what cerveteca has to offer. the calamari is cooked perfectly, crispy, and goes great with the fried shishito peppers. the barbacoa tacos are the best! super authentic made me think i was visiting my grandparents. i really like that you can order the fresh oysters individually as well since i tend to be the only person who eats oysters when my friends and i come so i usually order about 3 to myself. for my entree i tend to stick to the ribeye steak and get the mac and cheese and root veggies as sides. the mac and cheese is always delicious i love that it has bacon chunks not bits and that it's pairs well with the steak. if you're ever around, stop by. i promise you won't regret it!!
