like a lot of other reviewers have been saying, cerveteca is a great space with great potential. however, to me it fell flat in too many areas. it seems like the highlight of this place is the $1 oysters, but that's about it. some friends and i came out for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> last night, and i was excited because i love the food at eat drink americano next door and was hoping to find a similar experience in quality. first of all, what kind of <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> ends at 6? that isn't <span class="highlighted">happy</span> at all. especially with the location being so far removed from where anyone with an office job actually works, getting to enjoy anything before 6 is unrealistic. i work in downtown and all of the <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span> within walking distance and near metro stations go at least until 7. that, combined with the way everything is marked up so much after the clock hits 5:59, doesn't really give me any reason to trek out here. the menu includes all of your typical, trendy &quot;gastropub&quot; fare that you can see on any menu at any new restaurant these days; nothing special. many things i like, but the same things on any menu. i agree with another reviewer that a 10% decrease in price would make so much more sense. $13 for a small dish of mac and cheese with bacon ($11 without bacon) isn't very reasonable.my table ordered the calamari (which was lightly fried and served in a small frying basket), which was a little bland; i only had one. we also ordered the chips with guac and salsa, aforementioned mac and cheese, and a salmon taco. the mac and cheese was a baked dish of shells with not enough cheese melted on top, but my favorite part of the meal were the huge, thick, juicy chunks of bacon. as for drinks, the sangria was sweet and refreshing, the shot in a box of cold sake was really cool for the presentation, and the beer variety is pretty good. my friends who made it for the oysters told me that they were of excellent quality. i just hate leaving restaurants feeling like i got ripped off, which i did. service was pretty disappointing as well. these servers were my least favorite kind.... the kind who hover until you order, then disappear once you have your food. our water bottle sat empty most of the meal, and we had to go to the bar to ask for menus for friends who joined later, order drinks, and get our checks. a little more menu focus, reasonable price points, and more engaged service could really make this place something special.
