decided to try this spot out over the weekend after receiving an email from yelp mentioning some of the best places for macaroni. went during their brunch/<span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> transition. although we waited about 10-15 minutes to be seated while our table was being cleaned and had four different servers ask us if we had been helped (communication is key - everyone should be on the page regarding their customers), the rest of my experience was pleasant and the food definitely made up for any lack of service in the beginning. as suggested, i had to try their macaroni. orecchiette pasta, a mix of stringy, white cheeses and topped with goldfish crackers. i love the whimsical addition of the goldfish but the flavor is totally dependent on the cheese mix. perfection - seriously one of the best! i was so impressed with their mac, so i tried additional bar snacks like their smashed tater tots and jalape&ntilde;o hush puppies. the taters were deliciously salty bits of crunchy potato pancakes and served with garlic aioli and ketchup. the jalape&ntilde;o hush puppies looked like donut holes, but were dense corn fritters with jalape&ntilde;o bits that paired with the honey butter dip. these <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> bites went well with their white sangria. a refreshing white wine beverage with a hint of peach liqueur. i definitely recommend trying their <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> drinks and bites and all for a total reasonable price.
