i came here last week on a weekday for an early dinner. &nbsp;no reservations, and my party of three was seated instantly. &nbsp;they weren't too busy, so we had our choice between the patio and seating inside.our 6 p.m. dinner was timed perfectly with <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> (3-7 p.m. on weekends(!), 4-7 p.m. on weekdays). &nbsp;we started with the mac and cheese, the jalape&ntilde;o hush puppies, and the schnitzel (basically sliders).then we moved onto entrees. &nbsp;we got the cholo fried rice and the must soy hamburger helper. &nbsp;overall, i was a bigger fan of the hh than dinner. &nbsp;at $5 for the hh snacks and $5 for some drinks, it's a good bargain. &nbsp;the mac and cheese was okay - i liked that they had goldfish crackers crumbs as a topping, but other than that, the actual dish itself was pretty standard. &nbsp;i liked the hush puppies a lot more. &nbsp;they come with honey butter. &nbsp;the combination is flawless! &nbsp;the schnitzel was okay, too, but a little expensive at $3 for two or three bites. &nbsp;the fried mushroom, however, was thinly sliced and very crispy.the cholo fried rice did not live up to the hype. &nbsp;the carnitas were a nice touch, as was the fried egg and the avocado, but it didn't do enough to justify the price tag. &nbsp;i felt similarly about the hamburger helper. our waitress was right - i couldn't taste that the hamburger helper was fake meat, but that didn't mean the dish was good.service: &nbsp;our waitress was very friendly. &nbsp;she made small talk with us, checked in on us frequently, and overall made our dining experience more enjoyable. &nbsp;the busboys were very good about refilling our water too. &nbsp;a note about the space - it's new and nice. &nbsp;the walls are lined with wine bottles, and it's just dark enough that the restaurant is kind of intimate but not so dark you can't see. &nbsp;also, on the way to the bathroom downstairs, there's a small room that looks like it can be booked for private events. &nbsp;it looks like a lot of fun; there's even a movie projector and screen!bottom line: &nbsp;come here for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>!
