awesome ambience on the patio. pricey hit-and-miss food.1. mac n' cheese ($5 hh) - cheesy, thin-gooey, with crushed goldfish crackers on top. good size portion (like a cup of soup), tasty 2. hush puppies ($4 hh) - dense, a-ok but not great, has slivers of jalepeno for a little spice, honey butter was so-so (kinda plastic tasting is that weird?)3. smothered (in chili) hush puppies ($7 hh) - waitress didn't mention the extra charge was when she asked if we wanted it smothered or not... i assumed there would be a charge but when it almost doubles the price you'd think it'd be nice to know. chili should be called saucy brisket instead. 4. blistered peppers and fried anchovies ($8 not on hh) - <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> sized portion but normal appetizer price. taste was good but i only got 7 anchovies, smaller than my pinkie finger. peppers were blistered properly - warning some are very spicy others are not :) its kinda like a lotto game of spiciness5. cholo fried rice ($15 +$3 for an extra egg) - came with 1 sunny side up egg, that went well with the warm avocado slices and carnitas (choice of tofu or carnitas in the fried rice). unique blend of flavors, tastes like no other fried rice i've had, good. i like it but the price tag is a little steep- i'd order it again.. better value than the peppers/anchovies6. sangria (choice of white or red) ($5) - i got white, comes with peach slices, and apricot liqueur. good, sweet, and more of a nectar cocktail than a sangria (see photo). thick, kinda like they used kern's nectar in it. i like it! (but don't expect traditional sangria)
