ht before so i opted for the chicken pot pie a la mode. &nbsp;it was o.k. &nbsp;maybe the goat cheese was a little overpowering. &nbsp;my husband had the pork pie. &nbsp;the flavors were good but too salty. &nbsp;our friend marc had the drewben which he thoroughly enjoyed. &nbsp;i had a bite &amp; it was the best of the entrees that we ordered. &nbsp;our friend randy ordered the beet loaf...he said that it was between that &amp; the soy hamburger. &nbsp;i had to check his forehead because he is normally a carnivore. &nbsp;he asked danielle her honest opinion &amp; she suggested the beet loaf. &nbsp;randy enjoyed it. &nbsp;i had a bite &amp; although i like beets, i would get a real meat loaf any day! &nbsp;the service was excellent &amp; we would come back to try other options. &nbsp;they have a nice selection of beers on draught &amp; although i would never order it, they have a 40 oz. old english that comes in a paper bag. &nbsp;funny!
