this review is for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> only! &nbsp;great spot for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> with &nbsp;a couple girlfriends. &nbsp;arrived at 5pm on a friday, no line, no hassle, no cover. &nbsp;we walked in and the hostess gave us a token. &nbsp;i didn't really get it at first but later we gave our waitress the token and in return received a 35 cent martini!! nice! the martini of the day was a vodka gimlet, which was prepared nicely. &nbsp;a little on the sweet wide, but it was nice and strong. &nbsp;best welcome ever!they also had $5 appetizers during <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>. &nbsp;ordered the calamari and sliders (both came with generous serving of fries). &nbsp;both items were good, and the regular and sweet potato fries were good as well. &nbsp;only thing is the &quot;sliders&quot; actually was a &quot;slider&quot; ... 1 slider. &nbsp;yes, the drinks here are expensive. &nbsp;but during <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> it's 40% off any drink $13 or more. &nbsp;that's $7.80 for a nice fancy fairly strong drink. &nbsp;not the cheapest, but not bad. &nbsp;had the mistress and bermuda kiss. &nbsp;both tasted nicely and weren't too strong or weak. &nbsp;2 appetizers and 4 drinks later (including our nearly free drink) the bill was $27. &nbsp;not bad! service was mediocre. &nbsp;while the waitress was very friendly and <span class="highlighted">happy</span> to help us when we ordered, she didn't really come by often. &nbsp;maybe 3 times in 2 <span class="highlighted">hours</span>? &nbsp;it was kind of busy so maybe she had too many tables. &nbsp;worst come to worst, you can just order from the bar.i found the ambiance and decor to be really unique. &nbsp;dim lit, lots of different little rooms and caveats, waitresses in flapper style dresses, french music playing, you get a feel of mystery and sophistication. &nbsp;there weren't many seats available for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> as most of the tables were reserved for dinners. &nbsp;but we found a couple comfy chairs. &nbsp;if you're looking for a spot to be rowdy or a place to get drunk for cheap, this isn't really the place. &nbsp;but if you want to catch up with a couple friends, talk and relax over some drinks in dtla.... i definitely recommend this place. &nbsp;saw some people eating dinner here...not sure about that but will def be back for another <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span>!
