so, nikola tesla and thomas edison go into a bar...oh, you've heard this one. the edison is a glamourous place in downtown with impeccable design and a quirky sense about its pricing and <span class="highlighted">happy hours</span>. you could easily pay $50 for a straight scotch, or $0.35 for champagne. it depends on what time you go. it's small, but cavernous, expensive; yet features soup-kitchen era prices for its specials. all and all, it's a gem in los angeles and worth experiencing.
this place is amazing. it's located in what used to be the old edison building, hence the name. the old generators are still there. the decor is 1920's, and it does remind me of the glitz and glamour of that era. there's silent movies playing on various walls and hostesses dressed up in era costumes. the cocktails here are amazing. i recommend the edison martini and their gin cocktails. prices are steep, i recommend going during their <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> or sometimes on thurs night, they have a 35 cent drink special.
a few girlfriends and i ventured over to the edison for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> food/drinks on a friday. main reason we went was to score the 35 cent martini's they give out during <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> (5-7 pm)!we went pretty early and paid $5 for parking not even a block away. once you get to the entrance to the edison, you'll see bouncers who check id (so official!) outside of what looks like a bit shady. walk inside and wallah, beautiful. walk down a flight of stairs and become enthused about the beautiful interior design and architecture. self seating, wherever you can find a table (recommend you reserving one in advance though) or high top where people just lounge and be cool. for <span class="highlighted">happy hour</span> they have the 5 for $5 each deal and i would say everything on the menu is worth it! we (5 of us) ordered two grilled cheeses, chicken wings, sliders, and fries. they were all so delicious, especially the grilled cheese = melt in your mouth delicious. although at first we figured the portions were small, it was plenty of food to keep us &quot;just right&quot; for the rest of the night. the drinks were a bit pricier. i remember it being about $12 or $13?? personally don't think they were exceptional but good nonetheless. as for the 35 cent cocktails...apparently they change drinks every week or something? the day we went they served some cherry cocktail which tasted like robitussin bleghmy ratings are mostly on the actual loung/bar/restaurant and food more than the drinks. hope to experience the nightlife there soon though! ohhhh and even if you don't have to use it, i recommend you fancying yourself over to use the restroom. so cute and they have complimentary andes mint chocolates ;)
